<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06014155 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06014155 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PEACE; PROTEST; SF-BAY-AREA; LIST  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  As troops in the Persian Gulf prepare for battle, Bay Area peace activistswill be sponsoring vigils and demonstrations this week:; Today:  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  PROTESTS FOR PEACE  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Crisis in the Gulf;  See also related articles on pages 1A and 8A of thissection.  </MEMO><TEXT>  (box)6:30 a.m. Rush Hour Golden Gate Bridge Walk from Marin Vista Point.Participants advised to bring a &quot;body bag&quot; as a prop. Foothill Baptist Church,1347 Richardson Ave., Los Altos, opens the doors of its sanctuary from 6 a.m.to 10 p.m. for people to pray for a peaceful resolution of the Persian Gulfcrisis.; (box)10:30 a.m. Students at Santa Clara University join hands in apeace demonstration in front of Mission Church.; (box)Noon Peace Vigil byMilitary Family Support Network and Parents Against War, Broadway and 14thstreets, Oakland. Also at noon, Tri-Cities Ministerial Association will gatherat Mission San Jose, Fremont, for a prayer vigil. The mission bell will berung every 15 minutes until 1 p.m. -- midnight Jan. 15 in Baghdad, followed bya &quot;speak-out, teach-in&quot; at 7 p.m. at the Fremont Main Library, Paseo PadreParkway and Stevenson Boulevard, in the Fukaya A Room. A Vietnam veteran and aPalestinian will speak.; (box)5:45 p.m. &quot;Assembly of Conscience&quot; in the plazaat Market and San Carlos streets, San Jose, followed by a candlelight march.At 7 p.m., there will be an interfaith peace service at St. Joseph'sCathedral, Market and San Fernando streets, followed by an 8:30 procession toan all-night vigil at the federal building, 280 S. First St.; (box)7 to 10p.m. &quot;A Call for Peace&quot; at Pacific Cultural Center, Broadway and SeabrightAvenue, Santa Cruz. An evening to pray, sing and discuss the gulf crisis.;Tuesday:; (box)7 a.m. Attempted shutdown of federal building with 7 a.m.blockade and demonstration, 450 Golden Gate Ave., San Francisco, followed by a5:30 p.m. march in the Mission, 24th and Mission streets. If war begins, theEmergency Committee to Stop the U.S. War in the Middle East will gather at 5p.m. at  Powell and Market streets.; Wednesday:; (box)7 p.m. Town meetingsponsored by the Buddhist Peace Fellowship, Pacific School of Religion, 1798Scenic Ave. at La Conte, Berkeley.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910114  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  9A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  363  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday, January 14, 199100014155,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>